## Backend and data invariants

- Business logic lives in `/backend/app/services/`; routers only validate/resolve/call/respond.
- FastAPI routers do not contain streak, hearts, XP, crown, lock, goal, achievement, grading, or
  completion logic.
- The backend and SQLite own hearts, gems, XP, today XP, daily goal, streak, crowns, skill state,
  attempts, achievements, and leaderboard rank.
- Frontend state may cache API responses and manage transient UI only. Never calculate or persist
  learner progress in React, Zustand, or localStorage.
- All five exercise `options`, stored `correct_answer`, and submitted `answer` shapes exactly
  match `/docs/03_API_SPEC.md`.
- Start/retrieve/resume payloads never expose answers or hidden solution metadata.
- Seed validation, content-admin validation, and runtime grading reuse the same exercise-contract
  validation.
- Answer and completion mutations validate user ownership, attempt status, exercise order, and
  idempotency before changing state.
- A valid wrong answer loses at most one heart. Zero hearts fails the attempt atomically.
- Completion awards XP, streak, crown, unlocks, and achievements exactly once in one transaction.
- Use the injectable logical clock; never wait on or embed real wall-clock time in domain tests.
- Return real HTTP status codes with the standard error envelope; never return 200 for a failure.
- Use Alembic migrations. Runtime `create_all()` is not the migration strategy.
- Enable SQLite foreign keys on every connection.
- Resolve the simplified current learner centrally; never scatter a magic user ID.
- Preserve user data and migration history. Do not reset an unresolved database path.

## Functional honesty

Every required visible action must work end to end through the real backend. No hardcoded or
frontend-only hearts, XP, streak, crowns, rank, daily progress, lesson completion, or achievement
state is permitted.

Do not create:

- Buttons without working handlers.
- Links to `#`.
- Forms that report success without persistence.
- Fake refill/practice/settings/content-management actions.
- Client-side lesson advancement before a successful answer response.
- Seed-only counters disconnected from persisted attempts.

Only the deferred areas in the requirements may appear as placeholders: speech recognition/
pronunciation grading (playback TTS is required), payments/subscription, social features beyond
the leaderboard, and additional languages. Label them `Coming Soon` or `Demo Only` and make them
disabled or informational. Never hide a required feature behind a placeholder.

## Frontend model and skill routing

Use Sonnet for repository audits, architecture, database, backend, tests, fixes, routine frontend
API wiring, and variants of approved components.

Reserve Opus for visual judgment in Phases 8B, 8C, 9B, 10C, and 14. Do not spend Opus on
migrations, seed dictionaries, CRUD boilerplate, routine API wiring, or log/README formatting.

Exactly two project frontend skills exist:

```text
.claude/skills/ui-ux-pro-max/SKILL.md
.claude/skills/frontend-design/SKILL.md
```

- Use `ui-ux-pro-max` for UX hierarchy, responsive composition, accessibility, and usability
  audits when the phase requests it.
- Use `frontend-design` for original visual direction, shared 3D primitives, major screen
  composition, motion, and final screenshot polish when the phase requests it.
- Read the selected `SKILL.md` before applying it.
- Do not invent or reference `duolingo-3d-ui`, `frontend-qa`, or other project skills.
- Skill advice cannot override functionality, accessibility, API contracts, or project scope.

## Original 3D UI requirements

- Use the LingoQuest name and an original visual identity.
- Do not fetch, trace, bundle, or reproduce Duolingo logos, mascot art, audio, screenshots, or
  exact product copy.
- Implement tactile depth, pressed travel, semantic colors, typography, spacing, and motion with
  reusable design tokens and shared primitives.
- Reuse `Button3D`, `IconButton3D`, `Card3D`, `SkillNode3D`, `ProgressBar`, `ProgressRing`,
  `FeedbackSheet`, `Modal3D`, and `StatPill` patterns rather than duplicating one-off CSS.
- Support semantic controls, keyboard use, visible focus, non-color state cues, form labels,
  dialog focus, reduced motion, mobile targets, and responsive layouts.
- Judge visual phases from the running application and screenshots at approximately 360px,
  768px, and 1280px+, not source code alone.

## Verification and reporting

- Use isolated temporary databases for automated mutations.
- Test all five graders and UI interactions.
- Test refresh/resume, success, zero-heart failure, refill/retry, daily goal, leaderboard updates,
  achievements, content create/edit, user isolation, and duplicate/concurrent requests.
- Run relevant unit/integration/component/E2E tests, lint, typecheck, and production builds.
- Inspect browser console/network, keyboard behavior, loading/error states, reduced motion, and
  required viewports during frontend gates.
- Record commands and concise results in the handoff. Never claim unrun verification.
- Required features R-01–R-16 must be green before optional polish. R-17 remains open until
  delivery/deployment is explicitly authorized and verified.

## Repository and external-action safety

- Preserve a dirty worktree and unrelated edits.
- Do not use destructive reset, checkout, clean, or broad deletion.
- Do not commit secrets, `.env`, local databases, caches, dependency folders, or build output.
- Do not create commits, push, open pull requests, deploy, create external resources, or send
  messages unless the user explicitly requests that action.
- Deployment is currently deferred. Do not create provider configuration, hosting resources,
  domains, or production secrets until explicitly authorized.
